    schema:dateModified "2015-06"^^xsd:monthYear ;
    schema:description """The NATSISS was first collected in 2002 as a follow on from the 1994 National Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Survey. The NATSISS collects detailed information on the social and cultural experiences of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples. The last NATSISS in 2014-15 collected information on a range of topics, including:

    language and culture
    social networks and wellbeing
    health
    education
    work
    crime and justice
    housing
    stressors.



 """ ;
